libvalacore is an ambitious effort to build a powerful quasi-standard library
for the Vala language.

Vala has a solid GLib/GObject foundation, but lacks the kind of rich,
batteries-included standard library that developers in Java, Go, Python,
or OCaml take for granted. libvalacore fills that gap: it provides intuitive,
consistent, and well-tested APIs for file I/O, collections, string processing,
encoding, cryptography, networking, concurrency, and much more â€” all designed
to feel natural in idiomatic Vala.

Our goal is to make Vala a language where everyday programming tasks can be
accomplished with a single import, without hunting for scattered third-party
packages or reinventing the wheel.

== Namespaces ==

 * [[Vala.Io]] - File I/O, path, string, buffered I/O, and scanner operations
 * [[Vala.Lang]] - Language-level utilities (Objects, Os, Process, Signal)
 * [[Vala.Parser]] - Argument parsing
 * [[Vala.Collections]] - Collection types, Stream API, and functional utilities
 * [[Vala.Math]] - Mathematical functions and random number generation
 * [[Vala.Time]] - Date, time, duration, and stopwatch
 * [[Vala.Encoding]] - Base64, Hex, JSON, CSV, XML, TOML, YAML
 * [[Vala.Compress]] - Gzip and Zlib compression
 * [[Vala.Archive]] - Zip and Tar archive handling
 * [[Vala.Crypto]] - Hash, HMAC, and UUID
 * [[Vala.Net]] - HTTP client, socket, URL, and IP address
 * [[Vala.Concurrent]] - Thread pool, channel, future, mutex, and semaphore
 * [[Vala.Log]] - Structured logging
 * [[Vala.Test]] - Test assertions and benchmarking
 * [[Vala.Regex]] - Regular expression matching
 * [[Vala.Conv]] - Type conversion utilities
 * [[Vala.Config]] - Configuration file parsing (Properties, INI)
 * [[Vala.Event]] - Event emitter and listener pattern
 * [[Vala.Validation]] - Input validation
 * [[Vala.Errors]] - Error handling utilities
 * [[Vala.Unicode]] - Unicode character operations
 * [[Vala.Text]] - Template engine
 * [[Vala.Format]] - Number formatting
 * [[Vala.Runtime]] - Runtime information and system properties

